{
  "stem": "4361.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Traub's interview.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we were on the train back to Sighet.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The memory is very vivid of the trains coming from east full of the wounded soldiers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I don't know what I saw then.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know whether I felt-- I couldn't have possibly felt sorry for-- for-- I-- for German uniforms.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because by that time, it was very clear that they were the Amalek, the enemy of the people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I particularly remember one face-- blonde hair, face bandaged.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I don't think I had hatred in my heart, but I know that I didn't feel, oh, poor soldier.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because I remembered my brother, Moshe [NON-ENGLISH] telling what he told us about what he saw in-- in Russia-- in occupied Russia, I should say.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I knew that my brother, Alex, was still in-- in that brigade, and God knows what might happen to him even though he was still in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And as I said, by then there was something in the air which was terrifying, which was panicky, and it was Amalek.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Amalek came to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so the memory of those soldiers, wounded soldiers, was not one of pity or sorrow, that much I know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then when I got home the plunging into the abyss began.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because by that time, the law was unrestricted, unequivocally, anti-Jewish, anti-Semitic, anti, anti, anti-Jewish, all promulgated by the Hungarian government.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And this is what it consisted of.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "First of all, they took away all businesses from Jews, no two ways about it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I remember coming home and seeing my father-- I think we arrived back to Sighet during the day, and it was very strange for me to see my father in the middle of the afternoon being at home.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They took away his business.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
